snippet.title: Tech is getting more gay-friendly
snippet.description:
* James Lazar is married to a man. He won't buy anniversary cards that picture a man and a woman. He didn't want his Facebook page to show those symbols, either.
http://www.cnn.com/2012/07/03/tech/social-media/facebook-gay-marriage-icons/index.html

snippet.title: Yahoo punches up pages with Facebook
snippet.description:
* People who use both Facebook and Yahoo will be able to link those accounts and share updates and messages across platforms thanks to a major redesign rolled out by Yahoo on Monday.
http://www.cnn.com/2010/TECH/social.media/06/07/yahoo.facebook/index.html

snippet.title: Zuckerberg: No Facebook phone in the works, but new products coming
snippet.description:
* Facebook has been quiet for the past six months, but only because it's been working on new products. No, one of them is not a Facebook Phone.
http://www.cnn.com/2012/09/11/tech/mobile/zuckerberg-techcrunch-disrupt-talk/index.html

snippet.title: Mark Zuckerberg gives his take on 'The Social Network'
snippet.description:
* Despite previous statements that he had no plans to see "The Social Network," Facebook founder and CEO Mark Zuckerberg did, in fact, watch the film on the company's field trip to the movies last Friday.
http://www.cnn.com/2010/TECH/social.media/10/07/zuckerberg.social.network.mashable/index.html

snippet.title: Facebook to make mobile users download Messenger
snippet.description:
* Mobile users who have gotten used to chatting with their friends via Facebook will soon have to make sure they've downloaded the social-media giant's app designed specifically for that.
http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/15/tech/social-media/facebook-messenger-app/index.html

snippet.title: Salsa legend Cheo Feliciano dies in car wreck
snippet.description:
* Puerto Rican salsa legend Jose Luis "Cheo" Feliciano, a giant of the genre, died in a car crash early Thursday morning in San Juan, police said. He was 78.
http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/17/showbiz/cheo-feliciano-obit/index.html
